The paper deals with the maximum independent set problem in an arbitrary undirected graph, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The paper uses a technique developed by Ford and Fulkerson for the finite partially ordered sets, which is related to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.DS). The paper also involves constructing a special digraph, which is related to computational complexity (cs.CC) and graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper proposes an algorithm for solving the problem, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
